02 Feb 2014 01:14






The idea is, if people know that Ba-Ka attempted to gain immortality, they're going to start digging. The Foundation knows little to nothing about the mage. If they start digging, they could find some record or legend that refers to how Ba-Ka attempted to gain immortality, and that would be very, very, bad. Therefore, the safest route to go is to simply erase Ba-Ka from memory. If no one knows about the immortality-crazed pharaoh, then no one's going to go looking for how he tried to gain immortality.







